  "prompt": "Why does stars are not showing in my clash of clans map when I win on fighting with the other random players ?",
  "response": "In Clash of Clans, stars are earned based on your performance during an attack. However, these stars are typically displayed on the battle results screen rather than your main village map. Here are a few reasons why you might not be seeing stars:\n\n1. **Battle Results Screen**: Stars are shown after the battle on the results screen. You will see 1, 2, or 3 stars based on the damage percentage and destruction of the opponent's Town Hall.\n\n2. **Profile and Attack Logs**: You can see the stars you've earned in your profile under attack logs or in the war log if you're part of a clan war.\n\n3. **Victory Points**: On the main village map, the stars are not displayed directly. Instead, you can check your trophy count, which is affected by the stars you earn in multiplayer battles.\n\n4. **Game Interface**: Sometimes, graphical glitches or delays can cause information not to appear immediately. Restarting the game might help resolve these issues.\n\n5. **Connection Issues**: Ensure you have a stable internet connection, as connection problems might cause the game to not update properly.\n\nMake sure you're checking the right places for your stars and focus on the battle results and logs to track your performance.",
